tech.mcprison.prison

Class Prison

  • java.lang.Object
    • tech.mcprison.prison.Prison
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PluginEntity

    public class Prison
extends java.lang.Object
implements PluginEntity
    Entry point for implementations.

    An instance of Prison can be retrieved using the static get() method, however in order to use the core libraries, you must call init(Platform) with a valid Platform implementation.

    Since:
    API 1.0

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static Prison get()
        Gets the current instance of this class.

        An instance will always be available after the implementation invokes the init(Platform) method.

        Returns:
        an instance of Prison.

      • init

        public boolean init(Platform platform)
        Initializes prison-core. In the implementations, this should be called when the plugin is enabled. After this is called, every getter in this class will return a value.

        Note that modules should not call this method. This is solely for the implementations.

      • deinit

        public void deinit()
        Finalizes and unregisters instances in prison-core. In the implementations, this should be called when the plugin is disabled.

      • getDataFolder

        public java.io.File getDataFolder()

        Specified by:

      • getLocaleManager

        public LocaleManager getLocaleManager()
        Returns the LocaleManager for the plugin. This contains the global messages that Prison uses to run its command library, and the like. Modules have their own LocaleManagers, so that each module can have independent localization.
        Returns:
        The global locale manager instance.
